# ── Syncthing conflict artifacts (Gotcha #34, v1.1.7) ───────────────────
# Syncthing emits *.sync-conflict-<timestamp>-<peerid> when two machines
# edit the same file before sync converges. They must NOT enter git or be
# scanned by dual-source / sanitize gates. Inspect manually then delete.
*.sync-conflict-*
.syncthing-quarantine-*/
# v1.4.0 explicit (Gotcha #35): Syncthing chunked-transfer staging files.
# These are also caught by the generic `*.tmp` rule lower in this file, but
# listing the pattern here explicitly makes intent obvious to maintainers and
# lets audit tooling enforce "no .syncthing.*.tmp may persist" without relying
# on the generic *.tmp catch-all.
.syncthing.*.tmp

# ── Build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-version release directories (e.g. Release/git_release_skill-v0.9.11/)
Release/*/
# Top-level release artifacts
Release/*.skill
Release/*-source.tar.gz
Release/checksums.txt
Release/latest
Release/sbom.cyclonedx.json
Release/TOKEN_USAGE.md
Release/README.md
Release/INSTALL.md
Release/TEST-SCENARIOS.md
Release/LICENSE
Release/CONTRIBUTING.md
Release/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
Release/SECURITY.md
Release/ROADMAP.md
Release/SKILL.md
Release/RELEASE_NOTES.md
Release/install.sh
Release/scripts/
Release/references/
Release/assets/
Release/.sanitize-ignore
# NOTE: Release/CHANGELOG.md is NOT excluded — it's the accumulate changelog
*.skill
*.tar.gz
checksums.txt

# ── Self-release mirror ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The release pipeline enforces root scripts/ against this tracked bundle
# mirror. Other generated skill workspaces remain local-only.
skills/*
!skills/gitx-release/
!skills/gitx-release/**

# ── Private / dev working memory (not for public) ────────────────────────
# HANDOFF.md is user-level project memory per the handoff skill convention.
# Kept locally for Claude Code to read; never pushed to public remote.
# The handoff v2 four-piece + migration backup are the same class of
# git-orthogonal working memory — ignore them exactly like HANDOFF.md.
HANDOFF.md
HANDOFF.archive.md
HANDOFF.md.bak
HANDOFF.md.pre-v2-backup
GOTCHAS.md
Handoff_Logs/
Handoff_Decisions/
Handoff_Logs.archive/

# Internal review / research docs (not for public)
REVIEW.md
GitHub_STANDARD_ANALYSIS.md

# ── Claude Code / editor local state ─────────────────────────────────────
.claude/
memory/
.cursor/
.vscode/
.idea/

# ── OS / editor noise ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.bak
*.tmp

# ── Shell / test scratch ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
tests/.tmp/
*.log

# i18n translation cache (per-file content-hash keyed; regenerated on demand)
.i18n-cache/

# ── OMC working memory ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.omc/

# gitx-init/gitx-sop generate project-local .gitx/ — never ship it
.gitx/

# gitx-sop per-release GitHub publish worktree — has its OWN .git (public
# mirror only). Transient, rebuilt every publish; must never be tracked by
# the private repo, scanned by repo guards, or staged into a tarball.
.github-publish-wt/

# pyenv local pin — machine-local toolchain state, never a shippable input.
# release.sh rsync staging ignores .gitignore, so it is ALSO on release.sh's
# explicit --exclude list + .sanitize-ignore (codex P2, v1.9.6 five-facet).
.python-version

# ── graphify knowledge graph + local Claude instruction (not for public) ──
# graphify-out/ is a knowledge graph BUILT FROM the private working-memory
# set above (HANDOFF / Handoff_Logs / Handoff_Decisions / GOTCHAS / .omc):
# its graph.json + GRAPH_REPORT.md materialize that internal tacit knowledge,
# so it is the same not-for-public class. CLAUDE.md is local Claude Code
# instruction, read locally like HANDOFF.md but never pushed public. Same
# triple-exclude as .python-version: gitignore + release.sh --exclude +
# .sanitize-ignore (rsync staging ignores .gitignore).
CLAUDE.md
graphify-out/
